Wilhelm Frick is nominated to the Interior Ministry[? if old_prussia_leader == "Schleicher": —both in the Reich and in Prussia?]. Gregor Strasser takes the vice-chancellorship—a title in name only. [? if prussia_leader == "Goerdeler":  Although the <span style="color: #6A1E1E;">**DSU**</span> would’ve preferred Strasser installed in Prussia, Goerdeler stays on—as Schleicher’s loyal puppet and as a concession to the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>. ?]

At the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis’</span> insistence, Hjalmar Schacht is brought in as an independent to head the Economic Ministry.

To compensate for the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>’s loss of influence, they're given an additional Ministry without Portfolio. Not that the <span style="color: #000000;">Center</span> can complain—not with Bracht in charge.